sentences.chinese: 大家好，我是保罗D爱奥利欧。

sentences.english: 17From Miletus, Paul sent to Ephesus for the elders of the church.
sentences.chinese: 保罗从米利都打发人往以弗所去，请教会的长老来。

sentences.english: Paul, then, would seem to be contradicting Christ.

sentences.english: Octopus oracle Paul is predicting Germany will be defeated by Spain at the World Cup semifinal.

sentences.english: Paggy tell Paul, hot and sour soup is very delicious.

sentences.english: But another is the fact that Paul fears for the lost.
sentences.chinese: 但另一方面则是保罗为失落的人而感到惧怕。

sentences.english: Paul wants Christians to be governed by common sense that looks out for their fellow brother or sister.
